### View Separation Pattern

```php
// ✅ GOOD - View only displays data
<?php
$user = $userService->getCurrentUser();
$stats = $statCalculator->calculateFinalStats($user->getId());
?>
<div class="stat-card">
    <p>Chi: <?php echo htmlspecialchars($stats['chi']); ?></p>
</div>

// ❌ BAD - Don't put SQL or calculations in views
<?php
$db = Database::getConnection();
$damage = $attack * 1.5; // NO - calculations belong in services
?>
```

## Best Practices

- Always suggest improvements if architecture can be cleaner
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use dependency injection for testability
- Keep methods small and focused
- Use meaningful variable and method names
- Document complex game mechanics (ELO formulas, damage calculations, tribulation formulas)
- Design for extensibility from the start
- Consider performance for multiplayer scenarios
- Use transactions for multi-step operations
- Implement proper error handling and logging
- All calculations must be server-side
- Never trust client-provided values
- Maintain monolith structure - avoid overengineering
- Keep code modular but within monolith boundaries
